# UDS Master Workflow

## BUMP FIRST — Change Second — Finalize Last

This is NOT a post-hoc checklist. It is a mandatory three-phase workflow.

### Phase 0: BEFORE you start — is this even your call?

If the request is going to modify any file under **`uds-docs/uds/`**
(tokens, component CSS, spec.json, examples, schemas, status.json,
changelog.json, impl.json, components.json, version.json), stop and
re-read `.cursor/rules/uds-source-of-truth.mdc`. That directory is
Figma's source of truth and is almost never agent-modifiable; the
authorized write paths are the named Figma-sync skills
(`import-figma-tokens`, `sync-figma-component-spec`,
`sync-figma-component-status`, `link-figma-nodes`, `new-component`) or
an explicit user-directed revert toward verified Figma parity. If the
work doesn't fit one of those, surface findings rather than apply
edits.

This check sits BEFORE the SITE bump on purpose — there's no point
running `bump-site.sh` if the proposed change shouldn't happen at all.

### Phase 1: BEFORE making any changes

When you receive a request that will modify ANY file in `uds-docs/`, your FIRST action must be:

1. **Run `bash uds-docs/bump-site.sh`** — this script uses the system `date`
   command to compute the correct version, then updates all 3 locations
   (`index.html` display, `index.html` inline `SITE_VERSION`, `version.txt`)
   automatically. NEVER manually set the date or version number.
2. Read the script output to get the new version string.
3. Add a stub `SITE_CHANGELOG` entry to **`uds-docs/docs/data/site-changelog.js`**
   using the version and date from the script output. (This file is imported by
   `app.js`; the legacy in-file `SITE_CHANGELOG` array inside `app.js` was
   moved out during the Phase 3c restructure.)

**WHY:** The date in the conversation system header is from when the
conversation STARTED, not the current date. It can be days or weeks stale.
The bump script uses the system `date` command as the ONLY source of truth.
NEVER guess, calculate, or remember dates.

### Phase 2: Make the actual changes

Now do whatever the user asked for. Edit CSS, HTML, JS, add components, etc.

### Phase 3: Finalize — canonical component-update round-trip checklist

After all changes are complete, run THIS exact checklist. Every named
Figma-sync skill (`sync-figma-component-spec`, `sync-figma-component-status`,
`link-figma-nodes`, `import-figma-tokens`, `new-component`) references this
section as its definition of "done." Do not duplicate the steps inside the
skill files; do them here.

1. **Fill in the SITE_CHANGELOG stub** in
   `uds-docs/docs/data/site-changelog.js` with concrete descriptions of what
   changed.
2. **Per-component changelog entry** — if you edited any file under
   `uds-docs/uds/components/<id>/` (`<id>.css`, `<id>.js`, `spec.json`,
   `status.json`, `examples/**`, `impl.json`, `playground.js`), you MUST add
   a corresponding entry to `uds-docs/uds/components/<id>/changelog.json` for
   the current UDS version. The only exemption is a pure revert toward
   verified Figma parity; in that case include `[no-changelog: revert toward
   Figma parity]` in the commit message and the `scripts/audit-changelog-currency.sh`
   audit will skip the component.
3. **Aggregate** — if you changed any per-component `changelog.json` or
   `uds/CHANGELOG.globalNotes.json`, run
   `bash scripts/aggregate-changelog.sh`. If you added or removed a
   component folder, also run `bash scripts/aggregate-components.sh`.
   `scripts/audit-aggregate-currency.sh` will fail CI if you skip this.
4. **Figma sync-state snapshot** — if the change was sourced from a Figma
   read (a Figma-sync skill ran, or you manually corrected `figmaNodeId` /
   `figmaPageNodeId` after a direct inspection), update
   `.cursor/figma/state/components.snapshot.json` (the relevant component's
   `componentSetNodeId`, `pageNodeId`, `variantProperties`,
   `nestedInstances`) and `.cursor/figma/state/last-sync.json` (bump
   `lastSuccessfulSync`, recompute `components.snapshotChecksum`).
   `scripts/audit-figma-sync-state-currency.sh` will fail CI if `spec.json`
   `figmaNodeId` / `figmaPageNodeId` disagree with the snapshot.
5. **Figma Release Notes sync** — if `uds/CHANGELOG.json` changed (whether
   via a release or via mid-release per-component changelog additions), run
   the `sync-figma-release-notes` skill to rebuild the `Release Notes` frame
   on the `UDS Version: X.Y` page in BOTH `UDS Tokens` and `UDS Components`
   Figma files. Both files must contain identical text. This is allowed
   write scope #1 per `.cursor/rules/uds-figma-write-safety.mdc`.
6. **Cache-bust** — increment `?v=N` in `uds-docs/index.html` on any
   script/link tags whose source files changed:
   - `uds/uds.css?v=N` — bump if any tokens CSS or any component CSS changed
     (since uds.css `@import`s them).
   - `uds/uds.js?v=N` — bump if any component JS changed (since `uds.js`
     dynamically loads them).
   - `docs/app.js?v=N` — bump if `app.js` itself changed OR any of its ES
     module imports (`docs/data/*.js`, `docs/modules/**`, `docs/helpers/**`,
     `docs/pages/**` loader changes).
   - `docs/site.css?v=N` — bump if `docs/site.css` changed.
7. **Token-first CSS** — for any new CSS added under `uds-docs/uds/**`,
   verify it uses `--uds-*` tokens (no hardcoded colors, font sizes,
   spacings, radii). `scripts/audit-token-usage.sh` enforces this.
8. **Component checklist** — if a component was added or modified, verify
   the per-component folder is complete: `<id>.css`, `spec.json`,
   `status.json`, `changelog.json`, `impl.json`, `playground.js`,
   `examples/manifest.json`, ≥1 example HTML; sidebar link in `index.html`;
   `<div data-page="<id>">` placeholder. `scripts/audit-component-completeness.sh`
   enforces this.
9. **Content schema** — if you edited a component's spec, verify it was
   JSON-side at `uds-docs/uds/components/<id>/spec.json`, NOT a
   re-introduction of HTML in `index.html`. The Guidelines tab is rendered
   from the JSON.
10. **Page-chrome data-bind** — if you added a new component page, its
    `<div data-page="<id>">` block in `index.html` must have empty
    `<h1 class="sg-page-title" data-bind="title"></h1>` and
    `<p class="sg-page-desc" data-bind="description"></p>` placeholders.
    JS in `loadContent()` fills them from `spec.json`.
11. **Agent-toolchain docs** — if you edited any file under
    `.cursor/rules/`, `.cursor/skills/`, or `.cursor/agents/` (added a
    rule/skill/subagent, renamed one, removed one, or changed a rule's
    `description` field that affects its purpose), mirror the change in
    [`uds-docs/docs/pages/cursor-workflows.html`](../../uds-docs/docs/pages/cursor-workflows.html)
    in the same commit. `scripts/audit-agent-docs-currency.sh` blocks merge
    when a rule/skill/subagent file exists but isn't referenced on the page
    (and the reverse). Internal-only artifacts that intentionally aren't on
    the page belong in `scripts/audit-baseline.json` `audit-agent-docs-currency.toleratedFiles`.

## Why this order matters

The previous approach ("run checklist at the end") failed repeatedly because:
- Small changes felt "too minor" for the checklist
- By the time the edit was done, the mental task was "complete" and the
  checklist was skipped
- The version bump was disconnected from the actual edit

By bumping FIRST, the version is already incremented before any edits begin.
The changelog stub is waiting to be filled. These cannot be forgotten because
they happen before the work, not after.

The Phase 3 checklist additions (per-component changelog, aggregate, snapshot,
Figma Release Notes) are now enforced by CI audits, not just discipline:

- `scripts/audit-changelog-currency.sh` — fails if a component's source files
  (CSS/JS/spec/examples/impl/playground) have newer commits than
  `changelog.json`.
- `scripts/audit-aggregate-currency.sh` — fails if `uds/CHANGELOG.json` or
  `uds/components.json` differs from a fresh aggregate.
- `scripts/audit-figma-sync-state-currency.sh` — fails if any `spec.json`
  `figmaNodeId` disagrees with `components.snapshot.json` `componentSetNodeId`.
- `scripts/audit-css-api-table.sh` — fails if the Code-tab API table in
  `index.html` is out of sync with the actual `udc-*` selectors in the
  component's CSS.
- `scripts/audit-agent-docs-currency.sh` — fails if a rule/skill/subagent
  file under `.cursor/` exists but isn't referenced on
  `uds-docs/docs/pages/cursor-workflows.html`, or vice-versa (the page
  references a deleted file). Baseline-grandfathered via
  `scripts/audit-baseline.json`.
